# Sitecore Marketplace SDK General Rules

## Repository Overview

- This repository is a pnpm workspace TypeScript monorepo for the Sitecore Marketplace SDK.
- Main packages:
  - `packages/core` for secure postMessage transport, handshake, and request/event primitives.
  - `packages/client` for the public query, mutation, and subscription SDK used by Marketplace apps.
  - `packages/xmc` for generated XM Cloud modules plus hand-written entry points and experimental clients.
  - `packages/ai` for generated AI Skills modules plus hand-written entry points and experimental clients.
  - `packages/shared` for internal generator plugins and experimental client helpers.
- Prefer changes in the owning package instead of cross-cutting edits across multiple packages unless the behavior really spans packages.

## Core Working Principles

- Keep changes small, local, and type-safe.
- Follow existing public APIs and naming patterns unless the task explicitly requires an API change.
- Prefer fixing behavior at the source of truth instead of patching generated or duplicated outputs.
- Reuse existing helpers, types, and package boundaries before adding new abstractions.
- Preserve the existing monorepo layout and package ownership.

## Generated vs Hand-Written Code

- Do not hand-edit generated API clients under `packages/xmc/src/**/` or `packages/ai/src/**/` when the file header says `This file is auto-generated by @hey-api/openapi-ts`.
- If generated behavior is wrong, prefer editing:
  - `packages/xmc/generate-xmc.ts`
  - `packages/xmc/generate-xmc-experimental.ts`
  - `packages/ai/generate-ai.ts`
  - `packages/ai/generate-ai-experimental.ts`
  - `packages/shared/plugins/**`
- Treat `dist/**` as build output and avoid editing it.
- Treat most API reference docs under `docs/**` as generated TypeDoc output. Prefer updating source comments and doc generation inputs first.

## Build and Validation

- Package manager: `pnpm`.
- Workspace order matters: `core` before `client`, then `xmc` and `ai`.
- Prefer narrow validation over broad root builds.
- Common commands:
  - `pnpm test`
  - `pnpm lint`
  - `pnpm generate:module`
  - `pnpm generate:docs`
- For package changes, validate the touched package first.

## Contribution Rules

- Follow `CONTRIBUTING.md`.
- Include a changeset for PRs. Use an empty changeset for docs-only or guidance-only changes.
- Do not modify CI, workflows, lockfiles, or release configuration unless explicitly asked.
- Keep secrets out of the repository. Never add tokens, credentials, or `.env` values.

## Repo-Specific Examples

- Core communication patterns: `packages/core/src/index.ts`, `packages/core/src/post-message.ts`, `packages/core/src/handshake-manager.ts`
- Client SDK patterns: `packages/client/src/client.ts`, `packages/client/src/types.ts`, `packages/client/src/sdk-types.ts`
- Generator source of truth: `packages/xmc/generate-xmc.ts`, `packages/ai/generate-ai.ts`, `packages/shared/plugins/augmentation/plugin.ts`
- Experimental client helpers: `packages/shared/src/client-factory.ts`
